==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bitts
<hw>Bitts</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>bitte</ets>, Icel. <ets>biti</ets>, a beam. <?/87.]</ety>
<fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A frame of two strong timbers fixed
perpendicularly in the fore part of a ship, on which to fasten the
cables as the ship rides at anchor, or in warping. Other bitts are used
for belaying (<xex>belaying bitts</xex>), for sustaining the windlass
(<xex>carrick bitts</xex>, <xex>winch bitts</xex>, or <xex>windlass
bitts</xex>), to hold the pawls of the windlass (<xex>pawl bitts</xex>)
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bitume</ent>⟦br⟧
